Cisco_CPU_SmartM.Description: This check gives the CPU of the system as measured by instance of the CPU's and the overall CPU wide system memory
Cisco_CPU_SmartM.Name: CPU

Cisco_Health_SmartM.Description:
This check gives the health of all components in the system.
Default thresholds are "warning" for warning and "critical", "notFunctioning" for critical
Cisco_Health_SmartM.Name: Health

Cisco_Memory_Pool_SmartM.Description: This check gives the memory per memory pool
Cisco_Memory_Pool_SmartM.Name: Memory Pool

Cisco_Stack_SmartM.Description: This check monitors the status of the Cisco Stack.
Cisco_Stack_SmartM.Name: Stack

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonFanState.Description: The current state of the fan being instrumented.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonFanState.Name: ciscoEnvMonFanState

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonFanStatusDescr.Description: Textual description of the fan being instrumented. This description is a short textual label, suitable as a human-sensible identification for the rest of the information in the entry.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonFanStatusDescr.Name: ciscoEnvMonFanStatusDescr

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonFanStatusIndex.Description: Unique index for the fan being instrumented. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonFanStatusIndex.Name: ciscoEnvMonFanStatusIndex

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplySource.Description: The power supply source. unknown - Power supply source unknown ac - AC power supply dc - DC power supply externalPowerSupply - External power supply internalRedundant - Internal redundant power supply
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplySource.Name: ciscoEnvMonSupplySource

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplyState.Description: The current state of the power supply being instrumented.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplyState.Name: ciscoEnvMonSupplyState

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplyStatusDescr.Description: Textual description of the power supply being instrumented. This description is a short textual label, suitable as a human-sensible identification for the rest of the information in the entry.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplyStatusDescr.Name: ciscoEnvMonSupplyStatusDescr

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplyStatusIndex.Description: Unique index for the power supply being instrumented. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonSupplyStatusIndex.Name: ciscoEnvMonSupplyStatusIndex

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureState.Description: The current state of the testpoint being instrumented.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureState.Name: ciscoEnvMonTemperatureState

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusDescr.Description: Textual description of the testpoint being instrumented. This description is a short textual label, suitable as a human-sensible identification for the rest of the information in the entry.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusDescr.Name: ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusDescr

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusIndex.Description: Unique index for the testpoint being instrumented. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusIndex.Name: ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusIndex

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusValue.Description: The current measurement of the testpoint being instrumented.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusValue.Name: ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusValue

Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureThreshold.Description: The highest value that the associated instance of the object ciscoEnvMonTemperatureStatusValue may obtain before an emergency shutdown of the managed device is initiated.
Cisco_ciscoEnvMonTemperatureThreshold.Name: ciscoEnvMonTemperatureThreshold

Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolFree.Description: Indicates the number of bytes from the memory pool that are currently unused on the managed device. Note that the sum of ciscoMemoryPoolUsed and ciscoMemoryPoolFree is the total amount of memory in the pool
Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolFree.Name: ciscoMemoryPoolFree

Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolFree_Total.Description: Indicated the total number of bytes available in the memory pool.
Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolFree_Total.Name: ciscoMemoryPoolFree_Total

Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolName.Description: A textual name assigned to the memory pool. This object is suitable for output to a human operator, and may also be used to distinguish among the various pool types, especially among dynamic pools.
Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolName.Name: ciscoMemoryPoolName

Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolType.Description: The type of memory pool for which this entry contains information.
Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolType.Name: ciscoMemoryPoolType

Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolUsed.Description: Indicates the number of bytes from the memory pool that are currently in use by applications on the managed device.
Cisco_ciscoMemoryPoolUsed.Name: ciscoMemoryPoolUsed

Cisco_cpmCPUMemoryFree.Description: The overall CPU wide system memory which is currently free.
Cisco_cpmCPUMemoryFree.Name: cpmCPUMemoryFree

Cisco_cpmCPUMemoryKernelReserved.Description: The overall CPU wide system memory which is reserved for kernel usage.
Cisco_cpmCPUMemoryKernelReserved.Name: cpmCPUMemoryKernelReserved

Cisco_cpmCPUMemoryUsed.Description: The overall CPU wide system memory which is currently under use.
Cisco_cpmCPUMemoryUsed.Name: cpmCPUMemoryUsed

Cisco_cpmCPUMemory_Total.Description: The total of the overall CPU wide system memory
Cisco_cpmCPUMemory_Total.Name: cpmCPUMemory_Total

Cisco_cpmCPUTotal5minRev.Description: The overall CPU busy percentage in the last 5 minute period. This object deprecates the object cpmCPUTotal5min and increases the value range to (0..100).
Cisco_cpmCPUTotal5minRev.Name: cpmCPUTotal5minRev

Cisco_cpmCPUTotalIndex.Description: An index that uniquely represents a CPU (or group of CPUs) whose CPU load information is reported by a row in this table. This index is assigned arbitrarily by the engine and is not saved over reboots.
Cisco_cpmCPUTotalIndex.Name: cpmCPUTotalIndex

Cisco_cswSwitchNumCurrent.Description: This object contains the current switch identification number. This number should match any logical labeling on the switch. For example, a switch whose interfaces are labeled 'interface #3' this value should be 3.
Cisco_cswSwitchNumCurrent.Name: cswSwitchNumCurrent

Cisco_cswSwitchState.Description: The current state of a switch: waiting - Waiting for a limited time on other switches in the stack to come online. progressing - Master election or mismatch checks in progress. added - The switch is added to the stack. ready - The switch is operational. sdmMismatch - The SDM template configured on the master is not supported by the new member. verMismatch - The operating system version running on the master is different from the operating system version running on this member. featureMismatch - Some of the features configured on the master are not supported on this member. newMasterInit - Waiting for the new master to finish initialization after master switchover (Master Re-Init). provisioned - The switch is not an active member of the stack. invalid - The switch's state machine is in an invalid state.
Cisco_cswSwitchState.Name: cswSwitchState

Cisco_hostName.Description: This variable represents the name of the host in printable ascii characters.
Cisco_hostName.Name: hostName

Cisco_whyReload.Description: This variable contains a printable octet string which contains the reason why the system was last restarted.
Cisco_whyReload.Name: whyReload
